  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nSPX is trading just 6 points above the massive +10.3B gamma wall at 6900, putting dealers in aggressive selling mode as they hedge long gamma positions - the recent \"wall_break\" and \"gex_surge\" events confirm heavy dealer flow is hitting the market right now. With spot above the 6852 flip strike in PIN regime, dealers will continue selling rallies and buying any dips, creating strong magnetic pull back toward the 6900 level. The thick positive gamma cushion from 6900-7000 (over 26B combined) should cap upside momentum, while the negative gamma pocket at 6800 provides a natural bounce level if we see any meaningful selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6900 with limited upside past 6950.",
